{
  "texts": [
    "Enhancing their modeling capacities by using a higher rank r could demand too much computation resources and tend to overfit, while aggressively setting r smaller may degrade model performance and lead to from-scratch re-training (Ding et al., 2023).",
    "Our hypothesis posits that by altering the internal representations of neural models rather than their connected weights, the fine-tuning process could be significantly more efficient.",
    "This is because that direct manipulation of the representations necessitates O(n) parameters, whereas adjusting their weights theoretically demands O(n 2) parameters, with n denoting the dimensionality of hidden representations.",
    "Turner et al.",
    "(2023) have demonstrated that the behaviors of neural models can be influenced by adding a \"steer vector\" to each hidden layer during inference."
  ]
}